# forbidden-terms.example (QUM-872) — COMMITTED TEMPLATE, placeholders only.
#
# Copy this to .sprawl/hygiene/forbidden-terms (which is GITIGNORED) and replace
# the placeholders with the real values you must keep out of this PUBLIC repo.
# NEVER commit the real list — the public repo must not contain the list of
# things it is hiding. This .example must itself stay free of any real term.
#
# scripts/guard-employer-leak reads the real list and blocks a commit (staged
# scan) or a CI run (whole-tree scan, `--all`) that introduces a forbidden term.
#
# Format — one term per line:
#
#   category:matchtype:term
#
#   category  = a short label reported in the violation message (the term is
#               NEVER printed; only the category + file:line is shown).
#   matchtype = ci     -> case-insensitive substring (use for the employer name)
#               exact  -> case-sensitive substring   (use for GUIDs / IDs / names)
#   term      = the literal string to forbid (may itself contain ':').
#
# Blank lines and lines beginning with '#' (after optional leading whitespace)
# are ignored. A Linear-style issue prefix such as QUM-123 does NOT match the
# full employer name and is therefore always allowed.
#
# Example entries (REPLACE the placeholders; do not commit real values):
#
# employer-name:ci:REPLACE_WITH_EMPLOYER_NAME
# cloud-subscription-id:exact:REPLACE_WITH_SUBSCRIPTION_GUID
# cloud-tenant-id:exact:REPLACE_WITH_TENANT_GUID
# resource-group:exact:REPLACE_WITH_RESOURCE_GROUP_NAME
# storage-account:exact:REPLACE_WITH_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME
# tag-value:exact:REPLACE_WITH_TAG_VALUE
